{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Aircraft taxiing agent",
        "tags": ["taxiing"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 has landed on runway 19R. The clearance to taxi in has been granted. The ground power unit, the air conditioning unit and the wheelchocks are ready. Please taxi the plane to gate A1.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-5.4-mini",
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000,
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200,
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "aircraft_taxi_manager",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I am in charge of aircraft taxi in to or out of the gate at the airport.
I require: flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
ground_clearance_type, ground_clearance_status.
I also check that ACU, GPU, and wheelchocks are ready before taxiing.
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Current flight status."
                        },              
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },  
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "ACU readiness status."
                        },
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "GPU readiness status."
                        },      
                        "ground_clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Ground clearance type: 'taxi in' or 'taxi out'."
                        },  
                        "ground_clearance_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Ground clearance status."
                        },             
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","flight_status","gate_id"] 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the top-level agent responsible for aircraft taxi at the airport.
Do not make things up. Use your own tools only.

CRITICAL: You are a sequential executor. Execute each step in order.
Do not return until you reach RETURN SUMMARY.

When you receive a request to taxi the aircraft:

STEP 1 — Verify flight status
  flight_status must contain 'landed', 'taxi', or 'blocks'.
  If not, report that the aircraft cannot taxi and stop.

STEP 2 — Resolve ground clearance (ONE call maximum)
  If ground_clearance_status already contains 'clear' or 'grant'
  (case-insensitive), skip to STEP 3.
  Otherwise call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_traffic ONCE with:
    flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status,
    assigned_runway_id, gate_id, ground_clearance_type='taxi in'.
  Wait. Extract and store ground_clearance_type, ground_clearance_status.
  If clearance not granted, stop and report failure.

STEP 3 — Resolve ground services readiness (ONE call, non-blocking)
  Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_readiness ONCE with:
    aircraft_type, gate_id.
  Wait. Extract acu_readiness_status, gpu_readiness_status,
  wheels_chocks_readiness_status.
  Call TrackerAPI to store all three.
  Continue to STEP 4 regardless of readiness values.
  Report any unready items in the final summary only.

STEP 4 — Execute taxiing
  Call aircraft_taxiing_agent with ALL of:
    flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
    ground_clearance_type, ground_clearance_status,
    assigned_runway_id, acu_readiness_status,
    gpu_readiness_status, wheels_chocks_readiness_status.
  Wait for the response from aircraft_taxiing_agent.
  CRITICAL: The response from aircraft_taxiing_agent is a plain string
  that IS the new flight_status value. Evaluate it directly:
    - If the response string contains 'on blocks' or 'block':
        → taxiing succeeded. Proceed to RETURN SUMMARY.
    - If the response does not contain 'block':
        → report failure: "STEP 4 FAILED: taxiing did not complete."
  Do NOT call TrackerAPI after this step.
  Do NOT read flight_status from sly_data or TrackerAPI here.
  The taxiing coded tool has already written flight_status='on blocks'
  into sly_data directly. Reading TrackerAPI would risk returning
  the stale incoming flight_status that was present before taxiing ran.

RETURN SUMMARY:
  flight_status is 'on blocks' — confirmed from aircraft_taxiing_agent response.
  Write this hardcoded value into the summary. Do NOT substitute a variable.
  *******************************
  * Summary of aircraft taxiing *
  *******************************
  ** flight number           **: [flight_number]
  ** aircraft type           **: [aircraft_type]
  ** gate id                 **: [gate_id]
  ** assigned runway id      **: [assigned_runway_id]
  ** ground clearance type   **: [ground_clearance_type]
  ** ground clearance status **: [ground_clearance_status]
  ** ACU readiness           **: [acu_readiness_status]
  ** GPU readiness           **: [gpu_readiness_status]
  ** wheelchocks readiness   **: [wheels_chocks_readiness_status]
  ** flight status           **: on blocks
            """,

            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_status": true,
                    }
                }
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "assigned_runway_id": true,
                        "ground_clearance_type": true,
                        "ground_clearance_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                    }
                }
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "assigned_runway_id": true,
                        "ground_clearance_type": true,
                        "ground_clearance_status": true,
                    }
                }
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "ground_clearance_type": true,
                        "ground_clearance_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools": [
                "aircraft_taxiing_agent",
                "TrackerAPI",
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_readiness",
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_traffic"
            ], 
        }, 

        {
            "name": "aircraft_taxiing_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I am the pilot in charge of taxiing the aircraft on the ground at the airport. 
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {"type": "string", "description": "Flight number."},   
                        "aircraft_type": {"type": "string", "description": "Aircraft type."},        
                        "flight_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Current flight status."},        
                        "ground_clearance_type": {"type": "string", "description": "Ground clearance type."},         
                        "ground_clearance_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Ground clearance status."},       
                        "assigned_runway_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Assigned runway id."},        
                        "gate_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Assigned gate id."},    
                        "acu_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "ACU readiness status."},         
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "GPU readiness status."},       
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."},        
                    }, 
                    "required": ["flight_number", "aircraft_type","ground_clearance_type","flight_status","assigned_runway_id","gate_id","gpu_readiness_status","wheels_chocks_readiness_status"] 
                },
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_taxiing.aircraft_taxiing.execute_aircraft_taxiing" 
        }, 

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {"type": "string", "description": "Flight number."},   
                        "aircraft_type": {"type": "string", "description": "Aircraft type."},     
                        "flight_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Flight status."},          
                        "gate_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Gate id."},     
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."},   
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Wheelchocks installation status."},   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "GPU readiness status."},   
                        "acu_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "ACU readiness status."},    
                        "ground_clearance_type": {"type": "string", "description": "Ground clearance type."},         
                        "ground_clearance_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Ground clearance status."},       
                        "assigned_runway_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Assigned runway id."},                   
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_taxiing.aircraft_taxiing.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
